<% content_for :title, "How It Works" %>
<% content_for :description, "Join Motzi Bread's weekly menu mailing list to preorder online — and pre-buy credits if you like for a discount on every loaf." %>

<article class="page-subscribe">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-text">
      <h1>How It Works</h1>
      <p class="lede">Want our bread on a regular basis? Sign up for our weekly menu email and preorder whatever looks good — no commitment. If you like, pre-buy credits for a discount on each loaf while supporting our business with funds up front.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <% unless Setting.accepting_subscribers %>
    <section>
      <span class="badge-soldout">Currently Sold Out</span>
    </section>
  <% end %>

  <section>
    <h2>The Weekly Menu</h2>
    <p>Create an account and we'll email you the menu each week. Preorder right from the email — preorders are due by 9pm the day before pickup. Pickup is from our storefront during regular business hours; preorders cannot be picked up from the farmers market.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why Buy Credits?</h2>
    <p>Credits feature per-loaf discounts, occasional special loaves, and guarantee you get your favorite loaf even when we're sold out for general sale. Pre-buying also provides financial stability to us as a neighborhood business. Win-win for both us and you!</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Credits -</h2>
    <p>Pre-buy credits up front and redeem them for loaves when you preorder. Credits cannot be used in store.</p>

    <p>1 credit = 1 loaf or several pastries. There are <%= count_in_words(@bundles.size) %> credit bundles:</p>
    <ul class="subscription-options">
      <% @bundles.each do |bundle| %>
        <li><%= subscription_option(bundle) %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>

    <p>Item selection includes occasional specials for credit holders. Challah and holiday items are not generally included for purchase with credits.</p>

    <p>Order regularly or not. Credits are meant to be used, however we understand that schedules shift. Use multiple credits in a week or none. Your credits will never expire.</p>

    <p>Questions? <a href="/contact">Shoot us a message</a>, we'd love to hear from you.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="cta-row">
    <a href="/users/sign_up" class="cta-primary">SIGN UP NOW</a>
  </div>
</article>
